    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/wcl/fbh/6046309516.html"></div>
        </div>
Cornerstone Restaurant Group is seeking strong leaders for Michael Jordan's Restaurant, opening in Oak Brook this spring. <br>
<br>
Candidates for the following positions are currently being sought to join our team in providing a polished, personalized experience for our guests:<br>
<br>
* Catering/Private Dining Sales Manager (See Expanded Description Below)<br>
* General Manager<br>
* Dining Room Manager<br>
* Sous Chef<br>
<br>
POSITION SUMMARY: The Catering/Private Dining Sales Manager solicits and books private, group dining ("SEOs") and other catering-related activities in an assigned restaurant; general responsibilities include sales generation, SEO paperwork coordination, and participation in marketing and sales activities.<br>
<br>
AREAS OF RESPONSIBILITY (including but not limited to): <br>
• Generates group dining sales revenues by soliciting past and future clients, making out of office sales calls and presentations to potential clients, hosting in-house client dinners and responding to event inquiry calls and emails <br>
• Produces and manages contracts, SEOs, menu proposals and other paperwork necessary for all group dining events <br>
• Coordinates the planning and execution of booked events to ensure guest satisfaction, including menus, billing instructions, floor diagrams, additional amenities, etc. <br>
• Ensures accurate and timely payment and recording of all SEO revenues and related deposits and resolves billing issues with guests <br>
• Uses, manages and maintains sales software programs and systems <br>
• Prepares and distributes reports on SEO activity, including PACE reports, lost sales reports, etc. <br>
• Regularly visits various groups including concierges, neighborhood associations, chambers of commerce, convention bureaus, etc. to inform of upcoming events and/or solicit business <br>
• Participates in marketing and sales efforts (including off-site events, print publications, etc.), in collaboration with the Marketing Team <br>
• Researches competition on a regular basis to provide price and menu comparison information <br>
• Attends various internal and/or external meetings relating to SEO sales and/or the operation of the restaurant <br>
• May perform related administrative functions such as website auditing, menu proofing, and/or reservation system management <br>
<br>
ABOUT THE QUALIFICATIONS<br>
<br>
TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS <br>
• Job-related skills/experience <br>
- minimum 1-2 years prior F&B sales experience in a restaurant of similar style/scope <br>
- prior hands-on experience performing the majority of the areas of responsibility described above <br>
<br>
• Guest focus <br>
- grateful for guests <br>
- passionate & humble about service <br>
- proud to work in the industry <br>
- finds ways to say yes <br>
- committed to quality service and/or food <br>
- dignified in conduct and appearance <br>
<br>
• Financial skills/experience <br>
- basic math skills <br>
<br>
• Systems skills/experience <br>
- prior experience with & good working knowledge of sales software; experience with POS and/or other restaurant-related systems (Avero, etc.) is a plus <br>
-  good computer skills (Word, Excel, Outlook at a minimum)<br>
<br>
Please reply to this email with your resume and cover letter, and indicate in the subject line which of the positions you are interested in. <br>
<br>
As part of Cornerstone Restaurant Group, employees of Michael Jordan's Restaurant will be an essential part of creating a guest-focused culture, and will in turn receive training, support, and mentorship to achieve the highest levels of hospitality and further their own development.<br>
    </section>

